N:ralphmode
D:[ralphmode] Cross-platform permission profile for Claude Code, Codex CLI, and Gemini CLI that lowers approval friction for `ralph` / `jeo` loops by separating repo-local settings, explicit rules, and hook-backed checkpoints. Key idea: use trusted repo-safe presets for normal work, reserve full bypass / YOLO for disposable sandboxes, and keep secrets plus destructive commands behind hard checkpoints.
G:ralph permissions automation claude-code codex-cli gemini-cli sandbox bypass trusted-folders approval-policy hooks jeo

U[5]:
  When approval popups break flow while repeatedly running ralph or jeo
  When you need one portable mental model for Claude Code, Codex CLI, and Gemini CLI permission behavior
  When you must separate repo-safe automation from true sandbox-only YOLO mode
  When expanding automation while keeping guardrails for .env, secrets, force-pushes, sudo, or destructive DB commands
  When you need to explain why Codex relies more on approval policy + prompt contracts while Claude/Gemini can use pre-tool hooks

S[6]{n,action,details}:
  1,Define-Boundary,Lock down the project root and denylist (.env secrets rm -rf sudo force-push destructive DB commands) first
  2,Choose-Settings,Choose a repo-safe vs sandbox-only preset for Claude Code Codex CLI or Gemini CLI
  3,Apply-Local,Prefer project-local config and trusted-folder or trusted-project scope over broad global defaults
  4,Write-Rules,Keep repo-only mutation scope secret/path denylists and CHECKPOINT_NEEDED rules separate from the preset
  5,Run-Verify,Run in order: boundary check -> settings preset -> rules contract -> ralph or jeo -> verify
  6,Review-Revert,If this was a temporary bypass revert it after work and document the applied profile for the team

R[4]:
  Portable model: settings choose the preset, rules define the boundary, hooks enforce the dangerous edges when available
  Claude and Gemini can use pre-tool hooks; Codex should rely on approval_policy + sandbox_mode + prompt-contract fallback
  For detailed per-platform templates, read only the required sections in references/permission-profiles.md
  Use full bypass only in disposable sandbox environments and never as the default for day-to-day repo work

E[4]{desc,in,out}:
  "Cross-platform repo-safe setup","Make ralph low-friction in one repo across Claude Code Codex and Gemini while keeping .env and destructive commands blocked","Chooses repo-local settings for each platform and preserves denylist plus checkpoint rules"
  "Codex checkpoint fallback","Codex should stop before force-push or sudo even when approval prompts are reduced","Uses approval_policy + sandbox_mode + CHECKPOINT_NEEDED prompt contract instead of pretending Codex has Claude-style pre-tool blocking"
  "Portable abstraction","Explain ralphmode in one model that covers Claude Codex and Gemini","Names settings rules hooks and shows at least one important platform difference"
  "False-positive route-out","I need Claude team orchestration or /autopilot behavior","Routes to omc because ralphmode is the permission/profile layer rather than the runtime anchor"
